{
  "doc_id": "58240",
  "text": "Methotrexate (MTX) is an anti-neoplastic and anti-inflammatory agent used to treat a variety of malignancies and rheumatologic diseases. In ophthalmology, systemic and intraocular MTX has been successfully used for indeterminate uveitis, sarcoid uveitis, primary CNS lymphoma, and non-Hodgkin's lymphoma. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Recently, small case series have reported promising results with intra-silicone injection of MTX after vitrectomy for advanced PDR. [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] The aim of the present study was to evaluate the outcome of intra-silicone injection of MTX at the end of pars plana vitrectomy for eyes with TMD or TRD/RRD.",
